As the first step of spider robot assembly, all servo motors must be set to their center position (usually 90 degrees). Upload a basic Arduino code to move each servo to this neutral position.

When you upload the centering code, the servos need power to move to and hold the 90-degree (neutral) position. If the robot is not powered on, the servos won’t respond, and you won’t be able to attach the servo horns accurately.

So the correct sequence is:

Upload the basic position of servo motors Arduino code.
  
Select the board and port. If the code does not upload, select the processor as ATmega328P (Old Bootloader). After that, upload the code.

Power on the spider  robot (make sure the servo  motors get power).
  
Let all servos move to the center position.
  
Place the leg parts as shown in the assembly image.
  
servo zero 1
Leg parts aligned and servo horns fixed at 90° position (up)
servo zero 2
Leg parts aligned and servo horns fixed at 90° position (front)
servo zero3
Leg parts aligned and servo horns fixed at 90° position (back)
  
Attach the servo horns while keeping everything still.
